        "#convert rgb image into gray scale\n",
        "image=cv2.imread('image.jpeg')\n",
        "\n",
        "grayscale=rgb2gray(image)\n",
        "fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(6,4))\n",
        "ax=axes.ravel()\n",
        "ax[0].imshow(image)\n",
        "ax[0].set_title(\"Original\")\n",
        "ax[1].imshow(grayscale,cmap=plt.cm.gray)\n",
        "ax[1].set_title(\"Grayscale\")\n",
        "fig.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "plt.savefig(\"/content/grayscale.jpg\")"

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "LJDFosCGWA96",
        "colab_type": "code",
        "outputId": "db93a04d-e547-48a1-c57d-30e2913f92ce",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 269
        }
      },
      "source": [
        "#convert to RGB\n",
        "image1=cv2.cvtColor(resized,cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n",
        "#reshape the image to a 2D array of pixels and 3 color values\n",
        "pixel_values=image1.reshape((-1,2))\n",
        "\n",
        "#convert to float\n",
        "pixel_values=np.float32(pixel_values)\n",
        "#define stopping criteria\n",
        "criteria=(cv2.TERM_CRITERIA_EPS+cv2.TERM_CRITERIA_MAX_ITER,100,0.2)\n",
        "#number of clusters (K)\n",
        "k=1\n",
        "compactness,labels,(centers)=cv2.kmeans(pixel_values,k,None,criteria,10,cv2.KMEANS_RANDOM_CENTERS)\n",
        "#convert back to 8 bit values\n",
        "centers=np.uint8(centers)\n",
        "labels=labels.flatten()\n",
        "#convert all pixels to the color of the centroids\n",
        "segmented_image=centers[labels]\n",
        "#reshape all pixels to the color of the centroids\n",
        "segmented_image=segmented_image.reshape(image1.shape)\n",
        "#show the image\n",
        "plt.imshow(segmented_image)\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ],
      "execution_count": 215,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "display_data",
          "data": {
            "image/png": "\n",
            "text/plain": [
              "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
            ]
          },
          "metadata": {
            "tags": [],
            "needs_background": "light"
          }

        "masked_image=np.copy(image1)\n",
        "#convert to the shape of vector of pixel values\n",
